<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-16413] [camel-kafka] Avoid committing offsets onPartitionsRevoked during shutdown when autoCommitOnStop is &quot;none&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-16413</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;During shutdown process, whenever a partition is revoked, `onPartitionsRevoked` method is called, which is forcing `commitSync`&#160; even when `autoCommitOnStop` is set to none.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;```&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;tt&gt;DEBUG org.apache.camel.component.kafka.KafkaConsumer: - onPartitionsRevoked: **-Thread 0 from topic **&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;DEBUG org.apache.camel.component.kafka.KafkaConsumer: - Forcing commitSync **-Thread 0 from topic ** with offset: 31621&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;```&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
